line_1: 'Till perjuries are common as bad pence,
line_2: And hast thou sworn on ev'ry slight pretence,

line_1: SMIT with the love of Honour, — or the Pence,
line_2: O'er-run with wit, and destitute of sense,

line_1: "But Debtor and Creditor brings in the Pence:
line_2: "You may rhyme till you're blind, what arises from thence?

line_1: I laugh off Spleen, and keep my pence
Than their Fathers, who rais'd it by Shillings and Pence.
line_2: Why Spirit — to shew they have much better Sense
